==English==

===Interjection===
'''Yo!'''
# (''slang'') A greeting similar to [[hi]].
#: ''Yo Paulie!  How's it going?''
# (''slang'') An interjection similar to [[hey]].
#: ''Yo, check this out!''
# (''military slang'') Present!
#: ''Sergeant: ''Smith? ''Private Smith: '' Yo!

===Proper noun===
'''Yo'''
# The Divine Mystery, a pantheistic conception of God found in [[Yoism]]

===Pronoun===
'''yo'''
# A proposed gender neutral alternative to [[he]] or [[she]]

